This paper discusses the application of immune-inspired algorithms to intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of algorithms and implementation of a software system suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of sensors and real-time events suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
